     fhir:status [ fhir:v "generated" ] ;
     fhir:div [ fhir:v "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n      <p class=\"res-header-id\">\n        <b>Generated Narrative: CodeSystem action-applicability-behavior</b>\n      </p>\n      <a name=\"action-applicability-behavior\"> </a>\n      <a name=\"hcaction-applicability-behavior\"> </a>\n      <p>This case-sensitive code system \n        <code>http://hl7.org/fhir/action-applicability-behavior</code> defines the following codes:\n      </p>\n      <table class=\"codes\">\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">\n            <b>Code</b>\n          </td>\n          <td>\n            <b>Display</b>\n          </td>\n          <td>\n            <b>Definition</b>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">all\n            <a name=\"action-applicability-behavior-all\"> </a>\n          </td>\n          <td>All</td>\n          <td>The applicability of each action is evaluated independently; if the applicability criteria for an action evaluates to true, it is applied.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">any\n            <a name=\"action-applicability-behavior-any\"> </a>\n          </td>\n          <td>Any</td>\n          <td>The applicability of each action is evaluated in order; the first action for which the applicability criteria evaluates to true is applied, and processing of the parent action stops.</td>\n        </tr>\n      </table>\n    </div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
  ] ; # 
